The paper deals with a problem in computational geometry, specifically the separability of points in the plane. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as likely sub-categories. The connection between separability and partitions suggests cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as a possible sub-category.
